parameters.text:
Engine Control Unit
You can adjust the "C" setting, which essentially controls the speed. 50 is safe, but you can experiment with it depending on how long you stay on planets.

If there is no fluid in the engine but it’s available in the tanks, you need to turn the system off at least once for it to function properly afterward.

blueprint.description:
This platform is capable of traveling between any planets without delays. The Aquilo <-> Fulgora route has been stress-tested for 1 hour with no stops, with only a small demand for rockets occurring. Same with Aquilo orbit hovering.
=
You can play around with Engine Control Unit, where you can tweak fuel consumption "C".
50 is ideal to make it running non-stop.
=
Factory stats:
Turret damage 140%
Rocket damage 280%
Asteroid productivity 30%
Steel plate productivity 30%
blueprint.label: Info

- Circuit Logic (nuclear reactor, collectors, crushers)
- System Status Panel
- Engine Control Unit
[color=200,120,120]=========================[/color]
blueprint.label: Specifications

blueprint.description:
Step by step guide to run Xulo space platform.
=
Step 1: Build a platform from blueprint "Xulo Bootstrap".
Step 2: Request ammo&cells
Step 3: Wait until 15-20k of each engine fluid.
Step 4: Start traveling. Vulcanus is preferable.
Step 5: During the flight, superforce build blueprint "Xulo".
Step 6: Remove solars.
Step 7: Continue traveling between planets. A few trips are more than enough.
=
After all steps are completed, your space platform is ready to serve!
Whole procedure takes around 30min
blueprint.label: Bootstrap guide

blueprint.description: If you don’t have access to the listed T3 modules and rare structures, you can use the "Xulo downgrade" planner (Accumulator isn't need). However, I cannot guarantee that everything will be fine on Aquilo with this setup.
blueprint.label: Downgrade
